o Introduction

Original words from Lee Luyang:
    "This is my first program under X-window systems. I have chosen GTK+
library, *only* because of chance. :) GTK+ is designed for the GIMP, so
I think it must be goot at graphics. I decide to port ACD See, which is
a very popular image viewer in M$ world, into Unix systems by GTK+. That
is where the name "GTK See" comes from. But the current release is too
simple, But I will keep working on it, whenever I have time." 

    GTK See's home page is located at:

    http://hotaru.clinuxworld.com/gtksee/ [invalid since a long time]
    
    http://gtksee.berlios.de/

    Visit this site for the latest version.

